                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17384905" author="tallison@mitre.org" created="Wed, 21 Jul 2021 13:49:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Should we try to detect robots.txt files as their own mime?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17384931" author="tallison@mitre.org" created="Wed, 21 Jul 2021 14:49:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=nick&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;nick&quot;&gt;nick&lt;/a&gt;, any recommendations? &lt;tt&gt;text/x-robots&lt;/tt&gt; subtype of &lt;tt&gt;text/plain&lt;/tt&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;LOL: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nextthing.org/archives/2007/03/12/robotstxt-adventure&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.nextthing.org/archives/2007/03/12/robotstxt-adventure&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17384966" author="tallison@mitre.org" created="Wed, 21 Jul 2021 15:58:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I added mime detection for robots.txt in &lt;tt&gt;main&lt;/tt&gt; with mime &lt;tt&gt;text/x-robots&lt;/tt&gt;.  We can change this before the next release if there are objections.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17384992" author="wastl-nagel" created="Wed, 21 Jul 2021 16:48:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The &lt;a href=&quot;https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-koster-rep/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;robots.txt RFC draft&lt;/a&gt; requires &quot;text/plain&quot; as media type. Would be sound more straightforward to just recognize a robots.txt file as &quot;text/plain&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17385061" author="hudson" created="Wed, 21 Jul 2021 18:46:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;FAILURE: Integrated in Jenkins build Tika &#187; tika-main-jdk8 #286 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://ci-builds.apache.org/job/Tika/job/tika-main-jdk8/286/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://ci-builds.apache.org/job/Tika/job/tika-main-jdk8/286/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-3489&quot; title=&quot;Robots.txt files frequently identified as message/rfc822&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;TIKA-3489&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;TIKA-3489&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &amp;#8211; add mime detection for robots.txt files (tallison: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/tika/commit/5e2a3c081b3867086e417cb5cb032cb12be3c19d&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/tika/commit/5e2a3c081b3867086e417cb5cb032cb12be3c19d&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;(edit) tika-core/src/main/resources/org/apache/tika/mime/tika-mimetypes.xml&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;(add) tika-parsers/tika-parsers-standard/tika-parsers-standard-package/src/test/resources/test-documents/testRobots.txt&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;(edit) tika-parsers/tika-parsers-standard/tika-parsers-standard-package/src/test/java/org/apache/tika/mime/TestMimeTypes.java&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="17385470" author="tallison@mitre.org" created="Thu, 22 Jul 2021 12:33:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Will change to &lt;tt&gt;text/plain&lt;/tt&gt; today unless &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=nick&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;nick&quot;&gt;nick&lt;/a&gt; chimes in with a different recommendation.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17385514" author="gagravarr" created="Thu, 22 Jul 2021 13:52:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not keen on us throwing away information we can easily return to users&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A subtype of &lt;tt&gt;text/plain&lt;/tt&gt; with a more specific set of information feels the right way to go to me. I assume that the draft uses &lt;tt&gt;text/plain&lt;/tt&gt; for compatibility with webservers which don&apos;t properly / at all support more specific types&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Most people who want to handle robots files differently are going to need a way to know that it is a robots file, so won&apos;t be helped by &lt;tt&gt;text/plain&lt;/tt&gt;. Most people handling &quot;all texty stuff&quot; will just take any &lt;tt&gt;text/&lt;/tt&gt; so won&apos;t care about the subtype. Something like &lt;tt&gt;text/plain; format=robots.txt&lt;/tt&gt; feels possible but not ideal. &lt;tt&gt;text/x-robots&lt;/tt&gt; seems a bit more preferable to me&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17385631" author="wastl-nagel" created="Thu, 22 Jul 2021 15:57:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=nick&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;nick&quot;&gt;nick&lt;/a&gt;: agreed, sounds plausible.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17385761" author="tallison@mitre.org" created="Thu, 22 Jul 2021 20:29:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So, I&apos;ll leave this as is &lt;tt&gt;text/x-robots&lt;/tt&gt; and backport to the 1.x branch?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17396043" author="wastl-nagel" created="Mon, 9 Aug 2021 13:24:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 to leave it as is. A backport definitely makes sense, in case a 1.28 release is planned.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17397462" author="tallison@mitre.org" created="Wed, 11 Aug 2021 16:26:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you, all!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17397511" author="hudson" created="Wed, 11 Aug 2021 17:30:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;UNSTABLE: Integrated in Jenkins build Tika &#187; tika-branch1x-jdk8 #144 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://ci-builds.apache.org/job/Tika/job/tika-branch1x-jdk8/144/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://ci-builds.apache.org/job/Tika/job/tika-branch1x-jdk8/144/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-3489&quot; title=&quot;Robots.txt files frequently identified as message/rfc822&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;TIKA-3489&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;TIKA-3489&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &amp;#8211; detect robots.txt files as text/x-robots (tallison: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/tika/commit/27e7eac5fc7c2122076237c191a2bd0aa2748aa4&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/tika/commit/27e7eac5fc7c2122076237c191a2bd0aa2748aa4&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;(add) tika-parsers/src/test/resources/test-documents/testRobots.txt&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;(edit) tika-parsers/src/test/java/org/apache/tika/mime/TestMimeTypes.java&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;(edit) tika-core/src/main/resources/org/apache/tika/mime/tika-mimetypes.xml&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
